snippet: At least 58 people have died in the last week in a brutal cold wave that has plunged temperatures to 17 degrees below zero in some areas.
abstract: At least 58 people have died in a brutal cold wave that has plunged temperatures to 17 degrees below zero in Eastern Europe; Ukraine is among the hardest-hit countries, with as many as 30 deaths there.
lead_paragraph: At least 58 people have died in the last week in a brutal cold wave that has plunged temperatures to 17 degrees below zero in some areas.

headline.main: At Least 58 Killed in Eastern European Cold Wave
